{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Basic tutorial: ``Interleaving`` class"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This class encodes all the information needed to figureout an interleaving between two ``MapperGraph`` instances. \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from cereeberus import ReebGraph, MapperGraph, Interleave\n",
    "import cereeberus.data.ex_mappergraphs as ex_mg\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We have two example Mapper graphs to work with. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'M_1')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "M1 = ex_mg.interleave_example_A()\n",
    "M1.draw()\n",
    "plt.title('M_1')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'M_2')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "M2 = ex_mg.interleave_example_B()\n",
    "M2.draw()\n",
    "plt.title('M_2')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can create an instance of the interleaving class to store all the relevant matrices and smoothed graphs. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "myInt = Interleave(M1, M2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Inside of the  `Interleave` class, we have lots of setup data ready to go. \n",
    "\n",
    "Internally, the two graphs are labeled as $F$ and $G$, and an interleaving itself is a pair of maps $\\phi:F \\to G^n$ and $\\psi: G \\to F^n$. \n",
    "\n",
    "First we have the two original graphs stored as follows. The $F$ graphs for $0$, $n$, and $2n$ are in a dictionary `myInt.F` with keys `['0','n','2n']`. (Note the `0` is a string, not an integer)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "myInt.F['n'].draw()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "F_0: {'nodes': 25, 'edges': 26}\n",
      "F_n: {'nodes': 23, 'edges': 24}\n",
      "F_2n: {'nodes': 22, 'edges': 22}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for key in ['0', 'n', '2n']:\n",
    "    print(f\"F_{key}: {myInt.F[key].summary()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Similarly, we have a dictionary of the $G$ graphs. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "G_0: {'nodes': 32, 'edges': 32}\n",
      "G_n: {'nodes': 32, 'edges': 32}\n",
      "G_2n: {'nodes': 32, 'edges': 32}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "for key in ['0', 'n', '2n']:\n",
    "    print(f\"G_{key}: {myInt.G[key].summary()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Matrices \n",
    "\n",
    "There are many matrices stored in the `Interleave` class, but since these are largely block matrices due to the function preserving restriction on the maps, we store these in the following structure. \n",
    "\n",
    "A block dictionary is a dictionary with keys as the integer function values for the relevant graphs. Each key $i$ maps to another dictionary with keys\n",
    "- `array`: the matrix for the $i$ th block\n",
    "- `rows`: A list of the vertices (or edges) in order represented in the rows of the matrix\n",
    "- `cols`: A list of the vertices (or edges) in order represented in the rows of the matrix. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Matrices for Maps Induced by Inclusion\n",
    "The first block matrices are the inclusion matrices, stored as a dictionary `Interleave.I`, which give the maps $F \\to F_n \\to F_{2n}$ and $G \\to G_n \\to G_{2n}$. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'rows': [8, 9],\n",
       " 'cols': [6, 7],\n",
       " 'array': array([[0., 1.],\n",
       "        [1., 0.]])}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# For example, the induced inclusion map from $F_n$ to $F_{2n}$ for the vertices is given by:\n",
    "myInt.I['F']['n']['V']\n",
    "\n",
    "# The block of the diagram sending vertices with function value 7 in $V(F_n)$ to vertices with value 7 in $V(F_{2n})$ is given by:\n",
    "myInt.I['F']['n']['V'][7]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Reading the output above, we see that vertex 6 in $F_n$ is sent to vertex $9$ in $F_{2n}$, while vertex 7 in $F_n$ is sent to vertex $8$ in $F_{2n}$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There are also commands for converting this block dictionary to a full matrix dictionary:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "dict_keys(['rows', 'cols', 'array'])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "I_matrix = myInt.block_dict_to_matrix(myInt.I['F']['n']['V'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Note that this returns a dictionary with the rows, cols, and array\n",
    "I_matrix.keys()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And for visualizing, we can use the draw function to plot the matrix with rows and columns labeled accordingly. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Induced Inclusion Map from $F_n$ to $F_{2n}$ for Vertices')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 552x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "myInt.draw_matrix(myInt.I['F']['n']['V'])\n",
    "plt.title(r'Induced Inclusion Map from $F_n$ to $F_{2n}$ for Vertices')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We also have the induced maps for edges. This can be found as follows, or the full matrix can be drawn directly using the `draw_I` command. Note that the third entry for edge labels comes from the `nx.MultiDiGraph` parent class. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "{'rows': [(10, 11, 0), (10, 12, 0)], 'cols': [(8, 11, 0), (9, 11, 0), (10, 12, 0)], 'array': array([[1., 1., 0.],\n",
      "       [0., 0., 1.]])}\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Induced Inclusion Map from $F_n$ to $F_{2n}$ for Edges with Function Value 8')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 720x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(myInt.I['F']['n']['E'][8])\n",
    "\n",
    "myInt.draw_matrix(myInt.I['F']['n']['E'][8])\n",
    "plt.title(r'Induced Inclusion Map from $F_n$ to $F_{2n}$ for Edges with Function Value 8')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Induced Inclusion Map from $G_0$ to $G_{n}$ for Edges')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 512x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# myInt.I['F'].keys()\n",
    "myInt.draw_I('G', '0', 'E')\n",
    "plt.title(r'Induced Inclusion Map from $G_0$ to $G_{n}$ for Edges')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Boundary Matrices"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We also have boundary matrices for each graph, where $B[v,e] = 1$ iff $v$ is a vertex of edge $e$.  Note that unlike the inclusion matrices, we don't have separate vertex and edge versions, and we don't have the nice block structure,  so this can be found as follows."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "dict_keys(['rows', 'cols', 'array'])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 13,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "myInt.B['F']['n'].keys()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 480x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "myInt.draw_B('G', '2n')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Distance matrix \n",
    "\n",
    "Following (our arXiv paper that we should cite), there is a distance between any vertices at the same level defined to be the amount of smoothing needed for the two vertices to be mapped to the same vertex. This block matrix is stored in `Interleave.D`. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "{'rows': [5, 6, 21], 'cols': [5, 6, 21], 'array': array([[0., 2., 4.],\n",
      "       [2., 0., 2.],\n",
      "       [4., 2., 0.]])}\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Here's the distance between the vertices at function value 8 in $F$\n",
    "print(myInt.D['F']['0'][8])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 31,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Distance Matrix for Vertices with Function Value 8 in $F$')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 31,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 480x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# and here's a visual for the distance matrix\n",
    "myInt.draw_matrix(myInt.D['F']['0'][8])\n",
    "plt.colorbar()\n",
    "plt.title(r'Distance Matrix for Vertices with Function Value 8 in $F$')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As before, we can easily draw the full distance matrix using the `draw_D` command. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 32,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 480x480 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "myInt.draw_D('G', '2n')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import networkx as nx\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import cereeberus.data.ex_reebgraphs as ex_rg\n",
    "M = ex_rg.torus()\n",
    "M.f = {v: 2*M.f[v] for v in M.f.keys()}\n",
    "M = M.to_mapper()\n",
    "M.draw()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "v1: 2, v2: 3\n",
      "v1: 3, v2: 2\n",
      "[[0. 4.]\n",
      " [4. 0.]]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "length = dict(nx.all_pairs_shortest_path_length(M.to_undirected()))\n",
    "\n",
    "val_to_verts = M.func_to_vertex_dict()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "vert_set = val_to_verts[6]\n",
    "D_i = np.zeros((len(vert_set), len(vert_set)))\n",
    "for i, v1 in enumerate(vert_set):\n",
    "    for j, v2 in enumerate(vert_set):\n",
    "        if i!=j:\n",
    "            print(f\"v1: {v1}, v2: {v2}\")\n",
    "            D_i[i, j] = length[v1][v2]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(D_i)\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{10: 0, 3: 1, 4: 1, 8: 2, 11: 2, 9: 2, 1: 3, 5: 3, 2: 3, 7: 4, 6: 4, 0: 5}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 21,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "length[10]"
   ]
  },
  {
